locations.Text: Burgos.#n#n      January 10th, 1987.  You are a serious guy, with a big personality; a hard-working and responsible person, used to take on whatever comes your way in order to maintain your work status. You are not a very sociable person and with the years, you have inevitably become an incorrigible misanthrope, making you a hermit, of a few words, inexpressive and hostile at times.#k#b  You tend to talk to yourself a lot and have a highly developed consciousness: you can rarely show off your social skills. In other words, people who occasionally approach you run away in fear.#k#b  Today is Saturday and apparently you have no plans except to enjoy your 48 hours of freedom; that's what you call weekends. It's 12:30PM, is a cold winter day and you're still in bed half awake, sluggish. The early mornings of the week weigh you down more and more and you feel unable to leave your warm nest under the flannel blanket.#k#b  It's decided... You turn around in bed with the firm intention of sleeping a little longer, but at that same moment the phone on the bedside table rings. Someone's decided for you that you must definitely wake up.

You leave home and take your car to the Sierra del Caurel; it's a long journey, but you like to drive and the road allows you to disconnect from your daily life.#n#n  After a few hours of steamed up windows and badly paved roads, you recognize the crossing that leads to the village where your parents used to live.#k#b  You've just arrived and the exhaustion begins to take its toll on you and you feel the numbness in your muscles after the long journey.#k#b  Suddenly you perceive a distraction; the road has a beautiful grove of trees on either side whose branches taper through the treetops, producing an overwhelming tunnel effect that always gave you a bit of a fright as a child.#k#b  When the fog lifted, you found the place unsettling and your imagination played tricks on you. The holy company, the airs and graces of the dead... A deep suggestion since you were a child allows you to imagine the silhouette of Urco's dog from the mist.#k#b  Perhaps this land of processions, rites and pilgrimages of penitents left a deep mark on your personality.

You're in the area around the family property. You contemplate the last glimmers of clarity that give way to the closed night. The icy wind whistles through the cypress trees that surround the farm and the scene is overwhelming.#k#b The house has two floors and from here you can see to the NORTH the old shed, to the SOUTH the garage and to the EAST the porch; the main entrance of the house.
The garage has a small concrete ramp and a cream painted galvanized metal door.

You're on the outside of the shack. It's a place where the sun never shines.#n#n The cement walls are covered with moss and it feels like they can't absorb any more moisture. Just thinking about it, all your bones go numb.#n#n The shack has a very old door, made of wooden slats with a greenish color. It's completely peeled off by the temper.

A pair of powerful spotlights illuminate the porch. You never liked those lights because they attracted a lot of insects on summer nights. It was impossible to be there without suffering the ferocious attack of a bloodthirsty mosquito.

You find yourself in the foyer, stripped of every detail and dressed only in the subtle glow of the outside lights. It is discouraging and does not invite you to enter its rooms.#n#n You can see the stairs that lead to the top floor, the toilet to the NORTH, the kitchen to the SOUTH, the living room to the EAST and DOWN is the wine cellar. In front of you, there is the console that you have stumbled upon.#n#n There seems to be no one in the house.

In the bathroom the atmosphere is charged, thick, so much so that the flame of the match has changed colour to a bluish green and begins to produce a flickering sparkle...#n#nYou feel that you don't want to be here and you begin to feel distressed.#n#nThe fragile light allows you to discover a switch on the wall.

The cellar. A narrow and humid place that gives off a penetrating aroma of deep excavated earth.#n#n On one of the walls stands out a moldy wooden wine rack and you can also see, a large stain on the wall and a still in the background..

You're in the kitchen. Where yesterday was a cozy place that gave you that warm feeling of home, today is a room where you invade a feeling of cold discouraging that comes from the moisture contained in the walls.#n#n You can see the sink, a sideboard with a door, a cupboard for food to the EAST and of course, the old washing machine, which with over 20 years, still serving.

The faint light of the match illuminates weakly the living room of the house.#n#n The room is wide and is presided over by a large stone lareira with a forge cassette. Your father installed it because it was no longer used for cooking on his embers and mainly because of the fear of sweet death that was so typical of village houses. From it, some tubes were born, designed to distribute the heat through all the rooms of the house.#n#n You can see a large display cabinet where some books, family ornaments and a majestic Murano glass dish were once stacked, which dressed the great celebrations with an elegance and glamour typical of high nobility.#n#n From here you can access a large backyard to the EAST.

The stairs that in the house are very old and give off a certain old aroma of linseed oil. The steps are made of wood, wide and blunt. Despite the fact that people were smaller in the past, it seems that an imposing staircase gave a status of opulence.#n#n You notice a snap under your feet; you look down and see a loose step.
You're in the pantry. Here is the cupboard that your parents used to store cans of food and some kitchen utensils.
The full moon governs the night and its clarity is reflected on the extensive grey wall of the courtyard, which stands imposing as the protective armour of the estate; impregnable.

You have entered what appears to be an old dormitory without ventilation or lighting, although there are signs of having been inhabited, as there is a straw bed, an old wooden bench that looks like it was made in another century and a porcelain urinal.
You are on the upper floor, where a spacious corridor leads to the bedrooms of the house.#n#n There is a door located to the NORTH and the corridor continues to the EAST.
You are in the center of the corridor; there is a door in the SOUTH and the corridor continues from EAST to WEST.
You are at the end of the corridor, the bedroom is to the NORTH or you can go back down the corridor to the WEST.
It's a large, austere room, with no decoration or ornament. You can see a large iron bed in the center of the room and the door to the bathroom that is located to the NORTH..

You are in the bathroom; it has a small vent in the ceiling, as well as a majestic bathtub, which makes you remember with nostalgia those funny bathrooms you had as a child. Your mother made you do it because you came from the street always full of mud.
You're in the second bedroom, this one is smaller than the first and has a very sober servant's bed. To the SOUTH is the bathroom. The lack of ornament is a bit disturbing.
You're in the bathroom. It's small but complete, it has an antique bathtub, a sink and a toilet. This place is anachronistic..

We are certainly in the master bedroom; there is a very large bed with a wooden headboard and to the NORTH is the bathroom. In the room there is a carpet on the floor and a small bedside table with a modern lamp. You notice something strange on the wall, but with the dim light from the match, you can hardly tell what it is..

A thermal bath with mosaicism is undoubtedly the most extravagant whim that the original owner of this house allowed himself; nowadays, it does not cease to surprise you every time you contemplate it. The bath is located next to a wall that shows the mosaic of the God Apollo.#n#n At this moment and for some reason that you do not know, it is full of water up to the edge.

You've entered what appears to be a cabinet. You can't explain what this room is doing here, but it makes your hair stand on end. You can see a medical stretcher with chains hanging from it and there is also a table with rusty surgical instruments. The floor has a big dark stain which is probably dried blood.#n#n The trap door you came in through closes and you can't go back through it anymore.

The child discovers a hiding place for you between the cypresses and the wall.#k#n#n It is a nook that seems to be built to respect the natural growth of the cypresses, but over the years the tree that grows in that place has not taken up all the space provided, leaving an entrance behind that prevents you from seeing what is inside.

You've entered the shack. An infected, damp place, where they used to keep rusty gardening utensils and some tools, but there's nothing like that here anymore. The soil is compacted and very dirty. In this place there is a very unpleasant smell of humidity and closing.#n#n At the bottom of the shack you can see a metal cabinet.

You've just entered the garage, a place where, as expected, there is no car. It smells of diesel and oil, but surprisingly the room is spotless. It's a place with white walls and a red epoxy paint floor with a grill in the middle. On the wall, despite the reduced visibility, you can see a tap and there is also a diesel generator.
You're on top of the toilet. From here you can access the cistern.

xmessages.Text: #k#n
The match has been consumed.#n
#n#n
It's a big bed and it looks very comfortable.#n
It's soft and warm.#n
It's a pine wood night table, with a lamp that lets in a lot of light and you can't look at it directly because it hurts your eyes. It's very clean and no scratches or scuffs.#n#n
There's a gondola phone on it and it won't stop ringing.#n
You turn on the lamp.#n
You turn off the lamp.#n
It's a lamp that shines a lot of light..#n
Come on!, no one's looking at the phone. He picks it up, hangs it up, takes it, but he never examines it. You're not a doctor!#n
#b#n
You're too sleepy to know where the sound of the phone is coming from, however, you reach around on the table and pick up.#n#n
Good morning, son. How are you?#n#n
Hello, father. Until you called me I was sleeping peacefully, lying in bed, trying to negotiate with Morpheus (the god of sleep and dreams) for a second round.#n#n

Tell Morpheus to wait a moment and listen: Remember that today we had arranged to meet here, in the mountains. We have something very important to tell you, so get up and leave the house, otherwise it's going to be very late..#n#n
Hmmm, if I am honest, I was so tired that I no longer remembered that we had to meet today. Okay, I'll be leaving now..#n#n
See you later, son, drive carefully. Bye bye.#n#n
Later, dad.#n
You're too sleepy to know where the sound of the phone is coming from, however, you grope around on the table and pick up.#n#n
Hello, father. Until you called me I was like a king, lying in bed, trying to negotiate with Morpheus for a second round.#n#n
See you now, son, drive carefully. Bye bye.#n#n
See you later, father..#n
Your father has already hung up. You better get off your ass and go EAST to get the car.#n

The sound comes from the bedside table and you're still in bed, listening to the phone ring, you're a bum!#n#nYou're not going to take it? What if it's important?#n#nWhat if they're the ones at the game store to notify you that they have Nemesis cartridge in stock again?#n

Your room is big, but the decoration is minimalist; a bed, a nightstand with a lamp and a closet is all that the room has to offer.#n#n As a pragmatic person, you use the room to sleep and the expendable ornaments.#n
The phone's still ringing. Aren't you going to pick it up? Are you going to keep sleeping?#n
Do you really want to keep sleeping?#n

You're a smart guy. Nothing in this world is going to break your moment of peace and quiet. Besides, you already had the day planned: shower, coffee, reading the news and then trying the new MSX games you bought in the game store.#n#n
You hang up the phone.#n
Don't you think you should answer the phone?#n
You can't leave the house naked. You have to get dressed first.#n
You shower and dress quickly: you know your father doesn't like to be kept waiting.#k#n#nYou take the car keys, lock the door and go straight to the building's garage.#k#n
#nYou close the house door and go straight to the building's garage.#k#b#n
You leave the house and take your car to the Sierra del Caurel; it is a long journey, but you like to drive and the road allows you to disconnect from your daily life.#k#b#n

After a few hours of foggy windows and badly paved roads, you recognize the crossing that leads to the village where your parents have the house.#k#b There is little time to arrive, exhaustion begins to take its toll on you and you feel the numbness of your muscles after the long journey.#k#b#n

You suddenly perceive a distraction; the path has a beautiful grove of trees on either side, whose branches taper through the treetops, producing an overwhelming tunnel effect that always gave you respect as a child.#k#b#n

When the fog lifted, you found the place unsettling and your imagination played tricks on you. The holy company, the airs and graces of the deceased... A profound suggestion from childhood allows you to imagine the silhouette of the dog of Urco in the mist.#k#b Perhaps this land of processions, rites and pilgrimages of penitents left a deep mark on your personality.#k#b#n
I think I got the music mixed up, sorry... follow to the EAST and let's forget about this.#n
You're driving, I don't think it's a good idea to examine anything right now.#n
You love the peace and quiet of the scenery as you drive. It's a long drive, but it has a certain charm.#n
We can't go that way, my sister has blocked the door and I can't do anything to open it.#n#n
That would happen to me if i came home drunk.#n
You just got here and now you want to leave?#n#nNo way!#n
You start the car and leave the house and stop just before leaving the village.#k#n#n
You're like the cows that watch the train go by, huh? You spent your money on a video game and finished it off like a headless chicken, I get the feeling you haven't understood any of the story.#n#n

YOU HAVE COMPLETED THE ADVENTURE#n#n RATING: Absolutely denied.#n#n You've finished the game without solving the main mysteries, you haven't even come close.#k#n We strongly recommend that you give the game another chance and pay a little more attention.#k#n
You start the car and just as you're about to leave the property, the kid shows up:#k#n#n
Here I say goodbye to you. I can't go with you because I can't leave the house.#k#n#n
I'm going to find my parents and explain to them what happened. I also need to know that they're okay.#k#n#n
The girl appears...#k#n#n
YOUR PARENTS ARE NOW WITH US.#k#n#n
IT WAS ME! Thirty years ago I told them never to come here again.#k#n#n
RUN! GET OUT OF HERE! HURRY!#k#b#n
You start the car quickly and leave the property with spinning tires.#nYou drive away from the house and a few hundred meters, you stop the car.#k#n#n
They killed my parents... The house is full of sadistic ghosts... I have no idea what they're doing there... I've come out alive by a miracle...#k#n#n
You will never forgive yourself for what happened to your parents, NEVER!#k#b#n#n
You go back to the exit of the village and you come across a car that looks familiar. The other car honks its horn.#k#n#n
Son! Son! It's so good to see you! I suspected you'd still be around.#k#n#n
DAD! Don't bother me! You're ALIVE! When I tell you what happened, you won't believe it.#k#n#n
I can imagine, don't worry... You've met the family that shows up every thirty years in the house, right? Thirty years ago they appeared to us and your mother almost had a heart attack...#k#n#n

The truth is that thinking back, they seemed to have unfinished business to solve, but your mother took me off her arm at that moment and told me not to even think about coming back.#k#nI had arranged to meet you today to try and solve the problem together, as I knew that just tonight the children in the house would appear again, but son, you were so late that I had to leave.#k#n#n
What are you talking about? Let's see, the children told me you were dead!#k#n#n
Really? What bastards! That's what they must have felt bad about us running out of there... Well what... A beer or what?#k#n#n
One or seven, but what about Mom?#k#n#n
Your mother has been drunk since noon; alcohol and anti-depressants are not a good combination.#nCome on, son, let's get out of here..#k#n#n
Yes, of course, let's go..#k#b#n
YOU HAVE COMPLETED THE ADVENTURE#n#n RATING: Sloppy.#n#n Of all the possible endings, this is one of the worst. You left the house without understanding any of the history.#n#n

The house is spectacular; it is made entirely of stone from the quarries of Folgoso do Courel, which where be cut by cheap worker hands and caused many injuries.#k#n#nOr maybe your parents already bought it built and had no idea how it was built.#n#nThe house has a big fireplace that in the winter burns day and night, burning the wood that your parents collect from the forest.#k#bIt has a nice front terrace, which you used to go out on in the summer for lunch or dinner.#n#n
You notice the house is a bit neglected, it's like it's been a while since you've had any visitors.#n
Your eyes hurt from the bright light.#n#n
I wouldn't do that again..#n
You insist on looking again and a hypnotic attraction makes you fix your eyes on the spotlights.#k#n#n
The lights go up in intensity and you are blinded and trip over something on the ground.#k#n#n You bang your head against the porch railing and blood gushes out of the gap.#k#n#n
You can't enter the house. The door is locked and you need the key.#n#n
Do you remember when your parents used to go for walks in the woods?, they used to hide a key somewhere.#n
All around you can see an old potted plant#g#f!#t, a doormat#g#fVWXY#t and a garden gnome#g#f9#t.#n#n
Are we examining them step by step or are you in a hurry to get in the house?#n
The pot#g#f!#t still contains soil and what in its good times was possibly a plant, which is dry.#n
I don't see anything like that.#n
Maybe it's better if you go slowly. You can't take so many things at once. You're not in a TV competition.#n
Take what! if you haven't looked at anything!#n
It's a classic doormat with the message 'WELCOME HOME' #g#fVWXY#t.#n
I don't see any of that.#n
Under the mat#g#fVWXY#t there's nothing special, except for a centipede that comes out when it's discovered.#n#n
Let's leave the mat #g#fVWXY#t in place and stop bothering the local wildlife.#n
Really, again? The key to the house isn't gonna show up on its own. Keep looking.#n
You try to catch the centipede but it outsmarts you and hides in a hole.#n#n
Do you think this was necessary?#n
It's disgusting..#n
It's not like you, but you throw the pot on the ground and after several bounces, it's placed right where it was.#n#n
That's strange! And besides, it's intact! What's it made of?#n#n
You leave the pot#g#f!#t in place carefully.#n#n
What a good son you are, if your mother saw you, she'd be proud of her baby. Now to the point, are you gonna get in the house or should we call the fire department?#n

He's a chubby gnome with a mischievous smile and an intense look. #? You examine it carefully; it seems to be made of plaster since it weighs little, possibly hollow inside. You look for the opening through which the object was introduced, its feet, but now they're sealed with plaster.#n#n
You can't open it, unless...#n
You can't break it with your hands, but what if you throw it on the ground?#n
Under the gnome's feet there was an opening at the time. Now there's plaster and there's no way to remove it without breaking the gnome.#n
You throw the gnome on the ground and it breaks into a thousand pieces. Apparently he was hiding a metal key #g#f7#t inside it.#n#n
Now, when your mother finds out that you've broken the gnome... She is gonna freak out!#n#n
My mother was very appreciative of the gnome.#n
You can't throw away something you don't have.#n
Después de tantos años, tus padres van a echar de menos al gnomo.#n
I think I got the music wrong, sorry... try to open the door and forget about it.#n
An impressive wooden porch presides over the entrance of the house, although it seems that no one has passed through here for a long time.#n

It's a solid, strong door. Like all the main doors, it opens with a key.#n#nNow you remember that you always wanted the doorbell to be fixed, because when everyone was in their rooms, no one could hear who was at the door.#n
You didn't understand that the bell was broken, did you?#n
Nobody answers your call.#n
You can't enter the house because the door is locked.#n
But do you remember, when your parents went for walks in the woods, they used to hide a key somewhere. Do you remember where?#n
You leave the flowerpot#g#f!#t in place.#n#n
You're already inside the house. It's cold. You tripped over the console in the hall.#n
Hello? Anybody home? #nI don't want to joke around because I'm gonna get pissed. And you know it! #k#n#b#n
No one's answering. The door slams behind you. It doesn't open anymore. It's stuck and therefore you're locked in.#n
Hahaha, with all the trouble you had finding the damn key. Fucking gnome! Speaking of keys, where did you leave your car keys, Marcos. because I don't feel them on me?#n
Just what I needed! No way out of this house and now also without my car keys#g#fIJ#t#k#n
Hahaha, with all the trouble you had finding the damn key. Fucking gnome! Speaking of keys, where did you leave your car keys, 'cause I don't feel them on me?#n
The stairs are very dark. Use something to light it up, please.#n
The kitchen is too dark, without light it's not a good idea to go in. You need something to light it up.#n
The room is very dark, without light you can not enter.#n
After the scare I got... I'm not going in there!#n
The toilet is very dark, without light you can not enter.#n
The door is locked, you can't open it.#n
Wait till I get the Super Mario Bros...#n

It is a wide hall and from this position you can see the toilet that is to the NORTH, to the EAST you can see the lounge, to the SOUTH you have the kitchen, DOWN is the cellar and UP are the rooms. You have a wooden console next to you; it has a drawer.#n
It's a beautiful wooden console with wrought iron legs. Your mother inherited it from her family. Your parents always keep a light fixture in the drawer for when the power goes out.#n
The console's still beautiful. You open the drawer and we go on?#n
The console is still beautiful. There's nothing to look at here anymore.#n
It's a wooden drawer with an iron handle.#n#n
If you close your eyes and wish very hard, it may open by itself.#n
You open the drawer and find a box of XXL kitchen matches#g#f+,#t.#n#n
There's nothing interesting on the console anymore.#n
There's nothing interesting in the drawer anymore.#n
The wine cellar is very dark, without light you can't enter.#n
You need the key to the wine cellar#g#f1#t to get in.#n
You open the wine cellar door.#k#b#n
We go upstairs to the foyer.#k#n
On one of the walls a moldy wooden wine rack stands out and you can also see a large stain on the wall and a still in the background.#n
On one of the walls there is a moldy wooden wine rack and you can also see the door on the wall that you discovered using the palette#g#fmn#t. There is a still in the background.#n
It's a wall with a big stain on it.#n
It's an old still that, because of its condition, must have been used a lot. You pay attention and discover that the still is located just above a trap door.#n#n
I'm sure this thing was put to good use.#n
You move the still and when you move it, you can see a trapdoor on the floor.#n
It is an old bottle rack made of wood that has a capacity of about 50 bottles. It is empty.#n#n
It's a shame there aren't any little bottles of wine left.#n
La mancha parece ser de yeso#n
Maybe I have something I can use to remove it and check what's behind it.#n
It's a wood and metal trapdoor that has a combination lock.#n
The lock is in very bad condition, it looks rusty and probably the mechanism needs a good lubrication.#n
You've greased the lock and the combination mechanism is working.#n#n
The oil can has been emptied#g#fFG#t and you throw it away..#n
You don't have anything to grease the lock.#n
The lock is rusty and the mechanism doesn't work. It is recommended to grease it.#n
The lock mechanism works, but you don't know the combination to open it.#n
You put the combination in the lock and open the trap door.#k#n
I can't believe it!#n#n
You scratch the stain with the palette#g#fmn#t and discover an outline on the wall.#n#n
It's a door! And by the way, we broke the paddle#g#fmn#t. What an ass you are!#n
You broke the paddle#g#fmn#t, but the door is visible. You can use it.#n#n
It's a metal door that connects the wine cellar to another place.#n#n
I have no memory of this door. Besides, it doesn't have a lock, so I'm sure it can be opened.#n
You open the door easily and you can see that on the other side is the garage.#k#n
You open the door easily and you can see that on the other side is the garage.#k#n#n

You've just entered the garage, a place where, as expected, there is no car. It smells of diesel and oil, but surprisingly the room is spotless, even though you have a very reduced visibility. It is a place with white walls and a floor covered with red epoxy paint with a grill in the middle. On the wall you can see a tap and there is also a diesel generator.#k#n#b#n
This is where it all happened! I remember it perfectly.#k#n#n
Have you been following me?#k#n#n
Yes! You've been good to me and I'll go with you to help you.#k#n#n
You told me something happened here. What do you mean?#k#n#n
One day I escaped from the house looking for help, because the Lord was beating my mother, my sister and me, but the Lord discovered me on the way to the village and brought me here.#k#n#n
So what happened?#k#n#n

Well, here was my mother and sister dead. He had killed them and the bodies were on the floor. The Lord made me watch while he cut them with an axe#g#f%&'#t and when he finished, he forced me to help him take them to the shack.#k#n#n

I'm so sorry you had to witness that atrocity. As for your mother and sister... In the corridor of the house I found a little girl who almost finished me off and there was someone else in the last room.#k#n#n

Yes, it was my mother and my sister. My sister is very angry because she saw Mom get killed before she did. Today it's been thirty years since everything happened and since no one has ever discovered what happened, every thirty years we spend a night in the house until the bodies are discovered.#k#n#n
Did you say you took the bodies to the shack?#k#n#n

Yes. There we buried them with a shovel#g#f()*#t and that's where the Lord killed me by finishing a shovel on my head... Which reminds me that the keys to the shack#g#f2#t are hidden somewhere in this garage, hold on a moment...#k#n#n
You watch as the child walks to the garage door, rises to the ground and grabs something from the top fence of the door.#k#n#n
Here they are. Now we can go to the shack, but you need the shovel#g#f()*#t to dig us out.#k#n#n
Got it! I have to find a shovel#g#f()*#t.#k#n#n
All right, well, I'll help you solve the crime.#k#n#n
I'll go with you. My sister has closed the door to the outside, but I'm opening it right now, the bad thing is that she's going to find out and we won't be able to open it again.#k#n#n
The child opens the garage door and you go outside.#k#n
There's no door here.#n
The trap door is under a still, it cannot be opened.#n
You can't open the trap door because there's a lock on it.#k#n
The lock is greased and looks better, but you don't know the combination to open it.#k#n
You put the combination in the lock and get the trap door open.#k#n
You put the combination in the lock and get the trap door open.#k#n#n
I feel like my mother is in here... The best thing is to make sure she doesn't see us and we shouldn't be distracted.#k#n#n
We must be careful.#k#n
